\pard\s29\qj\fi-720\li2160\sa240\nowidctlpar\frmtxlrtb Re:\tab Purchase of Membership Interests in Merchant Energy Ventures, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company that is wholly-owned by Enron North America Corp. and will be the purchaser of two General Electric 7EA combustion turbine generator sets under and pursuant to an agreement with General Electric Company\par 
\pard\qj\nowidctlpar\frmtxlrtb Ladies and Gentlemen:\par 
\par 
\pard\s26\qj\fi1440\sa240\nowidctlpar\frmtxlrtb This letter (this \ldblquote \plain\ul Agreement\plain\rdblquote ), when executed by the parties, Enron North America Corp. (\ldblquote \plain\ul ENA\plain\rdblquote ), a wholly-owned and indirect subsidiary of Enron Corp., and NorthWestern Generation I, LLC (\ldblquote \plain\ul NorSub\plain\rdblquote ), a wholly-owned and indirect subsidiary of NorthWestern Corporation (\ldblquote \plain\ul NorthWestern\plain\rdblquote ) (ENA and NorSub being referred to herein, collectively, as the \ldblquote \plain\ul Parties\plain\rdblquote  and, individually, as a \ldblquote \plain\ul Party\plain\rdblquote ), shall set forth the agreement between the Parties relating to the transaction (as more particularly described herein, the \ldblquote \plain\ul Transaction\plain\rdblquote ) pursuant to which NorSub will acquire membership interests (\ldblquote \plain\ul Membership Interests\plain\rdblquote ) in Merchant Energy Ventures, LLC (the \ldblquote \plain\ul LLC\plain\rdblquote ), representing 80% of the equity of the LLC, under circumstances in which (i) ENA owns Membership Interests in the LLC representing 20% of the equity of  the LLC, and (ii) the LLC is the purchaser of two General Electric 7EA combustion turbine generator sets (individually, a \ldblquote \plain\ul Turbine\plain\rdblquote  and, collectively, the \ldblquote \plain\ul Turbines\plain\rdblquote  or the \ldblquote \plain\ul GE Equipment\plain\rdblquote ), under and pursuant to an agreement, made and entered into as of the 31st day of May 2000, and referred to therein as Contract BD-2-00, and as amended, modified and supplemented by Change Order Number 1 (Addition of Chilling Coils in Inlet System) and by Change Order Number 2 (Add Storage of Unit #1) (such Change Orders being referred to herein as the \ldblquote \plain\ul Original Change Orders\plain\rdblquote  and such {\strike Agreement} {\b\uldb agreement}, as amended, modified and supplemented by the Original Change Orders, being referred to herein as the \ldblquote \plain\ul Original Turbine Contract\plain\rdblquote ), by and between E-Next Generation LLC, as purchaser (the \ldblquote \plain\ul Original Purchaser\plain\rdblquote ), Enron North America Corp., as agent (the \ldblquote \plain\ul Agent\plain\rdblquote ), and General Electric Company (together with its successors and assigns, \ldblquote \plain\ul GE\plain\rdblquote ), as seller, as assigned by the Original Purchaser and the Agent to the LLC and assumed by the LLC (the Original Turbine Contract, as so assigned and assumed, being referred to herein as the \ldblquote \plain\ul Turbine Contract\plain\rdblquote ).\par 
As of the date of this Agreement, (i) the LLC is wholly-owned by ENA, (ii) one of the Turbines has been delivered under the Original Turbine Contract and has been placed in storage (under circumstances in which GE retains the risk of loss) at storage facilities located as \softpage set forth on \plain\ul Schedule I\plain  attached hereto (such Turbine being referred to herein as the \ldblquote \plain\ul First Turbine\plain\rdblquote ), and (ii) the other Turbine is scheduled to be delivered under the Original Turbine Contract in February, 2002 (such Turbine being referred to herein as the \ldblquote \plain\ul Second Turbine\plain\rdblquote ).\par 
