\pard\s40\qj\fi1440\sa240\nop\tx2160\frmtxlrtb\plain\b{\plain\loch\f0 22.\plain\tab}Dispute Resolution\plain .\par 
\pard\s41\qj\fi1440\sa240\nop\tx2160\frmtxlrtb\plain\ul{\plain (\loch\f0 a)\plain\tab}Binding Arbitration\plain .  Any dispute, controversy or claim arising under or relating to this Agreement (referred to in this Section 22 as a \ldblquote \plain\ul Dispute\plain\rdblquote ), that is not resolved by mutual agreement within 30 days after the date that one Party notifies the other of such Dispute, shall be resolved by binding arbitration as provided herein, and judgment on an award rendered therein may be entered in any court of competent jurisdiction.\par 
\pard\s42\qj\fi1440\li720\sa240\nop\tx2160\nop\tx2736\frmtxlrtb{\plain (\loch\f0 i)\plain\tab}Arbitration shall be initiated by the delivery of a written demand for arbitration by the demanding Party to the other Party.  The demand shall set out the nature of the dispute and the resolution sought by the demanding Party.\par 
\softpage{\plain (\loch\f0 ii)\plain\tab}The respondent Party shall have twenty (20) calendar days (the \ldblquote \plain\ul Response Period\plain\rdblquote ) to respond to the demand, in writing, setting out its answer and/or counterclaims.\par 
{\plain (\loch\f0 iii)\plain\tab}After the arbitration demand and response have been exchanged, a three-member arbitration panel shall be selected as follows:\par {\strike (1)}\par 
\pard\s43\qj\fi1440\li1440\sa240\nop\tx2160\nop\tx2736\nop\tx3600\frmtxlrtb{\plain {\b\uldb (}\loch\f0 {\b\uldb A)}\plain\tab}No person may be selected or serve as an arbitrator who is employed by, or under the control or management of, either Party;\par {\strike (2)}\par 
{\plain {\b\uldb (}\loch\f0 {\b\uldb B)}\plain\tab}Each Party shall, within fifteen (15) calendar days after expiration of the Response Period, appoint one arbitrator from a list of at least 20 names of arbitrators located in the State of New York as such list is maintained by the {\strike AAA} {\b\uldb American Arbitration Association} (the \ldblquote \plain\ul Arbitrator List\plain\rdblquote ) and provide written notice of the appointment to the other Party.  If either Party fails or refuses to appoint an arbitrator during the period for doing so, the other Party may appoint the second arbitrator; and \par {\strike (3)}\par 
{\plain {\b\uldb (}\loch\f0 {\b\uldb C)}\plain\tab}The two arbitrators so chosen shall confer and, within thirty (30) calendar days after their appointment, mutually select a third arbitrator from the Arbitrator List.  If the Party-chosen arbitrators cannot agree on a third arbitrator, each of them shall, within the fifteen (15) calendar day period stated above, name three (3) choices from the Arbitrator List.  Of the three choices named by each arbitrator, the other arbitrator shall then reject two (2).  Lots shall be drawn to appoint the third arbitrator from the two remaining candidates.\par 
\pard\s42\qj\fi1440\li720\sa240\nop\tx2160\nop\tx2736\frmtxlrtb{\plain (\loch\f0 iv)\plain\tab}In addition to its authority to hear the dispute presented by the Parties, the arbitration panel may, subject to the terms of this Section 22, make rulings in connection with the procedures and timetable to be followed by the Parties hereunder.\par 
{\plain (\loch\f0 v)\plain\tab}Within fifteen (15) calendar days after the final appointment to the arbitration panel, the arbitration hearing shall proceed, subject to the following requirements and procedures:\par {\strike (1)}\par 
\pard\s26\qj\fi1440\li1440\sa240\nowidctlpar\frmtxlrtb {\b\uldb (A)}\tab The arbitration hearing shall be held in New York, New York, at a location mutually agreed by the Parties, or failing such agreement, at a location determined by the arbitration panel;\par {\strike (2)}\par 
{\b\uldb (B)}\tab Strict rules of evidence shall not be applied in the arbitration hearing.  The Parties may offer such evidence as they desire and the arbitrators shall accept such evidence and accord it such weight as the arbitrators deem appropriate.  Cross-examination of witnesses and rebuttal testimony shall be permitted; and\par {\strike (3)}\par 
{\b\uldb (C)}\tab Each Party may, but is not required to, submit one (1) pre-arbitration hearing brief (of not more than ten (10) pages (excluding exhibits)) no later than five (5) Business Days prior to commencement of the arbitration hearing, and may also submit one (1) post-arbitration hearing brief (of not more \softpage than ten (10) pages (excluding exhibits)) no later than ten (10) business days after the close of the arbitration hearing.  A copy of any brief submitted to the arbitration panel shall also be served on the other Party.\par 
\pard\s42\qj\fi1440\li720\sa240\nop\tx2160\nop\tx2736\frmtxlrtb{\plain (\loch\f0 vi)\plain\tab}After submission of any post-arbitration hearing briefs and within thirty (30) calendar days after the close of the arbitration hearing, the arbitrators shall render an award upon a majority vote, subject to the following requirements and procedures:\par {\strike (1)}\par 
\pard\s26\qj\fi1440\li1440\sa240\nowidctlpar\frmtxlrtb {\b\uldb (A)}\tab The arbitration panel shall weigh evidence and make its award, taking into account, to the extent it deems applicable, custom and usage of the industry; \par {\strike (2)}\par 
{\b\uldb (B)}\tab The arbitration panel\rquote s award shall be issued in writing and shall state the factual bases and reasoning of the award; and\par {\strike (3)}\par 
{\b\uldb (C)}\tab The arbitrators may award costs of the arbitration proceeding, excluding attorneys\rquote  fees and also excluding the costs apportioned pursuant to clause (vii) below; \plain\ul provided\plain , \plain\ul however\plain , that the arbitrators shall have no authority to award punitive damages or any other relief expressly disclaimed by the parties herein.\par 
\pard\s42\qj\fi1440\li720\sa240\nop\tx2160\nop\tx2736\frmtxlrtb{\plain (\loch\f0 vii)\plain\tab}Each Party shall pay the expenses of the arbitrator of its selection.  The amount or rate to be paid by the selecting Party shall be disclosed to the other Party upon engagement of the arbitrator. The Parties shall jointly and equally pay the reasonable expenses of the arbitrators-selected arbitrator.\par 
{\plain (\loch\f0 viii)\plain\tab}Except as may be required by applicable law, including, without limitation, federal or state securities laws, neither Party may disclose the progress, content, findings or award of any arbitration commenced or completed hereunder without the prior written consent of the other Party nor may the arbitrators disclose such information without the written consent of both Parties.\par 
{\plain (\loch\f0 ix)\plain\tab}All time limits stated in this Section 22 are for the convenience of the Parties and may be altered upon mutual agreement of the Parties.\par 
\pard\s41\qj\fi1440\sa240\nop\tx2160\frmtxlrtb\plain\ul{\plain (\loch\f0 b)\plain\tab}Sole and Exclusive Remedy\plain .  The procedures specified in this Section 22, shall be the sole and exclusive procedures for the resolution of any Dispute between the Parties arising out of or relating to this Agreement; \plain\ul provided\plain , \plain\ul however\plain , that a Party may seek a preliminary injunction or other preliminary judicial relief if in its judgment such action is necessary to avoid irreparable harm.  Despite such action, the Parties will continue to follow, in good faith, the procedures specified in this Section 22.  All applicable statutes of limitation shall be tolled while the procedures specified in this Section are pending.  The Parties will take such action, if any, required to effectuate such tolling.  Notwithstanding anything set forth in this Section 22, any Party hereto may bring an action in any court of competent jurisdiction to compel arbitration under this Agreement or to confirm or enforce (i) an arbitration award which resolves a Dispute or (ii) any judgment entered on such award.\par 
\softpage\pard\s40\qj\fi1440\sa240\nop\tx2160\frmtxlrtb\plain\b{\plain\loch\f0 23.\plain\tab}Further Assurances\plain .  The Parties agree (i) to furnish upon request to each other such further information, (ii) to execute and deliver to each other such other documents, and (iii) to do such other acts and things, all as the other Party may reasonably request, for the purpose of carrying out the intent of this Agreement and the documents referred to in this Agreement.\par 
{\plain\loch\f0 24.\plain\tab}\plain\b Interpretation\plain .  In construing this Agreement:\par 
\pard\s41\qj\fi1440\sa240\nop\tx2160\frmtxlrtb\plain\ul{\plain (\loch\f0 a)\plain\tab}Examples\plain .  Examples shall not be construed to limit, expressly or by implication, the matter they illustrate;\par 
{\plain (\loch\f0 b)\plain\tab}\plain\ul Including\plain .  The word \ldblquote includes\rdblquote  and its derivatives means \ldblquote includes, but is not limited to\rdblquote  and corresponding derivative expressions;\par 
{\plain (\loch\f0 c)\plain\tab}\plain\ul Controlling Provisions\plain .  Each {\strike Exhibit and} Schedule to this Agreement is a part of this Agreement, but if there is any conflict or inconsistency between the main body of this Agreement and any {\strike Exhibit or} Schedule, the provisions of the main body of this Agreement shall prevail;\par 
{\plain (\loch\f0 d)\plain\tab}\plain\ul Neutral Interpretation\plain .  This Agreement is the result of arm\rquote s-length negotiations from equal bargaining positions by both Parties.  It is expressly agreed that this Agreement shall not be construed against any Party, and no consideration shall be given or presumption made on the basis of who drafted this Agreement or any particular provision hereof or who supplied the initial form of this Agreement;\par 
{\plain (\loch\f0 e)\plain\tab}\plain\ul Severability\plain .  If any provision of this Agreement is held invalid or unenforceable, the other provisions of this Agreement will remain in full force and effect.  Any provision of this Agreement held invalid or unenforceable only in part or degree will remain in full force and effect to the extent not held invalid or unenforceable;\par 
{\plain (\loch\f0 f)\plain\tab}\plain\ul Headings\plain .  The headings and numbers of Sections of this Agreement are provided for convenience of reference only and will not affect its construction, interpretation or meaning; and\par 
{\plain (\loch\f0 g)\plain\tab}\plain\ul Time of Essence\plain .  With regard to dates and time periods set forth or referred to in this Agreement, time is of the essence.\par 
